        <style>
            .alert {
              padding: 20px;
              background-color: #f44336;
              color: white;
              opacity: 1;
              transition: opacity 0.6s;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
            }
            
            .alert.success {background-color: #04AA6D;}
            .alert.info {background-color: #2196F3;}
            .alert.warning {background-color: #ff9800;}
            
            .closebtn {
              margin-left: 15px;
              color: white;
              font-weight: bold;
              float: right;
              font-size: 22px;
              line-height: 20px;
              cursor: pointer;
              transition: 0.3s;
            }
            
            .closebtn:hover {
              color: black;
            }
            </style>
        
<h2> Weekly crime Alerts</h2>
<p>Click on the "x" symbol to close.</p>
<div class="alert">
    
  <span class="closebtn">&times;</span>  
  Indicates a dangerous or potentially negative action.
  
</div>
<div>
    <h2>This week</h2>
</div>

<div class="alert success">
  <span class="closebtn">&times;</span>  
  Frequent Patterns: There's been a frequent pattern of Theft and Rape on 3 occasions 
  Crime Incidence: 7 reports recorded
  Advice: Avoid leaving your valuables unattended. Stay aware of your surroundings, avoid isolated public areas.
</div>
<div><h2>Last week</h2>
</div>

<div class="alert info">
  <span class="closebtn">&times;</span>  
  Frequent Patterns: There's been a frequent pattern of Robbery and Rape on 4 occasions 
  Crime Incidence: 10 reports recorded
  Advice : Stay aware of your surroundings, avoid isolated public areas. Stay alert.
</div>
<div>
    <h2>last month</h2>
</div>

<div class="alert warning">
  <span class="closebtn">&times;</span>  
  Frequent Patterns: There's has been a frequent pattern of Robbery and Carjacking on 7 occasions Crime Incidence: 17  reports recorded
  Advice: Stay alert. Use alternating routes
</div>

<script>
var close = document.getElementsByClassName("closebtn");
var i;

for (i = 0; i < close.length; i++) {
  close[i].onclick = function(){
    var div = this.parentElement;
    div.style.opacity = "0";
    setTimeout(function(){ div.style.display = "none"; }, 600);
  }
}
</script>

